The paper deals with depth functions in nonparametric data analysis, which are commonly used in computational geometry and machine learning. The paper proposes two methods for approximating the planar halfspace depth and $\beta$-skeleton depth, which are fundamental concepts in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves dissimilarity measures and range counting problems, which are related to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), respectively. The paper also discusses the convergence of $\beta$-skeleton depth functions, which is a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
